aa(lp32
VSeeing this video of Gabby Giffords reminded me
p33
aVof the work of Dr. Gottfried Schlaug,
p34
aVone of the preeminent neuroscientists studying music and the brain at Harvard,
p35
aVand Schlaug is a proponent of a therapy called
p36
aVMelodic Intonation Therapy, which has become very popular in music therapy now.
p37
aVSchlaug found that his stroke victims who were aphasic,
p38
aVcould not form sentences of three- or four-word sentences,
p39
aVbut they could still sing the lyrics to a song,
p40
aVwhether it was "Happy Birthday To You"
p41
aVor their favorite song by the Eagles or the Rolling Stones.
p42
aVAnd after 70 hours of intensive singing lessons,
p43
aVhe found that the music was able to literally rewire
p44
aVthe brains of his patients and create a homologous
p45
aVspeech center in their right hemisphere
p46
aVto compensate for the left hemisphere's damage.
