aVI had just completed my undergraduate, and I was working
p69
aVas a research assistant at the lab of Dennis Selkoe,
p70
aVstudying Parkinson's disease at Harvard, and I had fallen
p71
aVin love with neuroscience. I wanted to become a surgeon.
